# VS Code Extension Development - Quick Reference Card

One-page cheat sheet for building VS Code extensions.

## Extension Activation Events

```typescript
// In package.json "activationEvents"
"onLanguage:javascript"              // When JS file opened
"workspaceContains:*.config.json"    // When file in workspace
"onCommand:myExtension.activate"     // When command run
"onView:myView"                       // When sidebar expanded
"onStartupFinished"                   // After VS Code starts
"*"                                   // ‚ö†Ô∏è SLOW - avoid!
```

## Core APIs Quick Lookup

| Feature | API | Use Case |
|---------|-----|----------|
| Inline hints | `CodeLens` | "X references", "Run test" |
| Highlighting | `Decoration` | Mark errors, warnings, todos |
| Hover info | `HoverProvider` | Show on mouse over |
| Auto-complete | `CompletionProvider` | Suggest code |
| Quick fixes | `CodeActionProvider` | Lightbulb menu |
| Linting | `Diagnostics` | Report issues |
| Navigation | `Tree View` | Sidebar explorer |
| Custom UI | `Webview` | Dashboards, panels |

## Extension Registration Pattern

```typescript
// src/extension.ts
import * as vscode from 'vscode';

export async function activate(context: vscode.ExtensionContext) {
  // 1. Register providers
  context.subscriptions.push(
    vscode.languages.registerHoverProvider('javascript', hoverProvider),
    vscode.languages.registerCodeActionProvider('javascript', actionProvider),
    vscode.languages.registerCodeLensProvider('javascript', lensProvider)
  );

  // 2. Register commands
  context.subscriptions.push(
    vscode.commands.registerCommand('extension.doSomething', () => {
      vscode.window.showInformationMessage('Done!');
    })
  );

  // 3. Listen to events
  vscode.workspace.onDidChangeTextDocument(event => {
    analyzeDocument(event.document);
  }, null, context.subscriptions);
}

export function deactivate() {}
```

## The 5 Must-Know Patterns

### 1. Debounce Pattern (Prevent Lag)
```typescript
let debounceTimer: NodeJS.Timeout;

vscode.workspace.onDidChangeTextDocument((event) => {
  clearTimeout(debounceTimer);
  debounceTimer = setTimeout(() => {
    analyze(event.document);  // Won't run until typing stops
  }, 500);  // 500ms after last keystroke
});
```

### 2. Cache Pattern (Reduce CPU)
```typescript
const cache = new Map<string, Result>();

function analyze(doc: vscode.TextDocument): Result {
  const key = `${doc.uri}:${doc.version}`;
  if (cache.has(key)) return cache.get(key)!;

  const result = doExpensiveWork(doc);
  cache.set(key, result);
  return result;
}
```

### 3. Lazy Activation (Fast Startup)
```json
{
  "activationEvents": ["onLanguage:javascript"],
  "main": "./out/extension.js"
}
```

### 4. Async Everywhere (No Freezing)
```typescript
async function handleCommand() {
  const result = await vscode.window.showQuickPick(['a', 'b']);
  await performAnalysis(activeEditor.document);
  vscode.window.showInformationMessage('Done!');
}
```

### 5. Error Handling (Don't Crash)
```typescript
try {
  const result = await analyze(doc);
  diagnostics.push(...result);
} catch (error) {
  console.error('Analysis failed:', error);
  vscode.window.showErrorMessage(`Error: ${error.message}`);
}
```

## Diagnostics (Linting)

```typescript
const diagnostics = new vscode.DiagnosticCollection('myLinter');

vscode.workspace.onDidChangeTextDocument((event) => {
  const doc = event.document;
  const issues: vscode.Diagnostic[] = [];

  // Find issues
  const text = doc.getText();
  if (text.includes('console.log')) {
    const range = new vscode.Range(0, 0, 0, 11);
    issues.push(new vscode.Diagnostic(
      range,
      'Unexpected console statement',
      vscode.DiagnosticSeverity.Warning
    ));
  }

  diagnostics.set(doc.uri, issues);
});
```

